From: Eric Allred
Subject: Re: [VB] RE: oil temp.

Jake Raby did back to back tests, and found higher head temps when the
Type III tin was used on a T I motor.

It's hard to argue when the same load (dyno) is put on the same motor,
in the same atmosphere conditions, and the only change made was the
addition of those tins.

One test is worth a thousand theories.
Just something to think about.

Eric Allred
